'''Charles Knight''' ({{circa}} 1808 &ndash; 3 September 1891) was a New Zealand doctor, public servant and botanist. He was born in [[Rye]], [[Sussex]], England in {{circa}} 1808. Knight was the country's inaugural [[Controller and Auditor-General of New Zealand|auditor-general]]. In New Zealand, he first lived in [[Auckland]] and when the government moved to [[Wellington]], he also relocated to the [[Capital of New Zealand|new capital]]. He died at his home in Wellington and is buried at [[Bolton Street Memorial Park]].<ref name="DNZB Knight">{{DNZB|Galloway|D. J.|1k14|Charles Knight|9 February 2017}}</ref>

