'''Heinlein''' is a crater in [[Promethei Terra]], [[Mars]].  Centered at 64.6 degrees south, 243.8 degrees west, it is 83&nbsp;km in diameter and is in the southeast end of the [[Hellas quadrangle]].  It forms a crater pair with [[Weinbaum (Martian crater)|Weinbaum]] as the southern rim touches that crater, that crater is in the Southern Polar Region.

Other nearby named prominent craters are [[Huxley (Martian crater)|Huxley]] to the west, [[Wells (Martian crater)|Wells]] to the east-northeast and [[Byrd (Martian crater)|Byrd]] to the east, the latter two are not of the Hellas quadrangle.

It is named after [[Robert A. Heinlein]], a leading [[science fiction]] author.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/2415?__fsk=-1521410232|title=Heinlein Crater|website=Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature, International Astronomical Union (IAU) Working Group for Planetary System Nomenclature (WGPSN)|accessdate=November 30, 2017}}</ref>

Heinlein helped to narrate [[The Moon Landing|the Moon landing]] with [[Walter Cronkite]] on CBS in 1969.  He was involved in the planning of the [[Strategic Defense Initiative|Star Wars Defense]] program in the 1980s.  Several of his novels involve Mars, especially ''[[Stranger in a Strange Land]]'', [[Red Planet (novel)|''Red Planet'']], and ''[[Podkayne of Mars]]''. Many [[NASA]] officials say that his works inspired them to enter the space industry.

