{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2016}} '''Nélida María Bacigalupo''' (born 1924) is an Argentine botanist, curator, and professor. She studied at the [[National University of La Plata]], and in 1953, she received her doctorate in Natural Sciences at the same university. She served as an investigator at the Instituto de Botánica Darwinion, [[San Isidro, Buenos Aires]]. Bacigalupo did her botanical research in Paraguay and Argentina.<ref name="JSTOR">{{cite web|title=Bacigalupo, Nélida María (1924–)|url=http://plants.jstor.org/stable/10.5555/al.ap.person.bm000000335|publisher=JSTOR|accessdate=19 August 2016}}</ref> She is a world authority on the [[Rubiaceae]] [[Family (biology)|family]]. She is a member of the Argentine Botanical Society, and was the honorary vice-president of the 33rd Argentine Botany Conference in 2011.
